===Etymology 2===
An alteration of Old English [[-ende]].

====Suffix====
'''-ing'''
# Used to form [[present participle]]s of [[verb]]s.
#:''making'' (as in ''You are making a mess.'')

====Translations====
{{top}}
*French: [[-ant#French|-ant]]
*Interlingua: [[-ante#Interlingua|-ante]], [[-ente#Interlingua|-ente]], [[-iente#Interlingua|-iente]]
{{mid}}
*Italian: [[-ando#Italian|-ando]] (''for verbs ending in [[-are#Italian|-are]]''), [[-endo#Italian|-endo]] (''for verbs ending in [[-ere#Italian|-ere]] or [[-ire#Italian|-ire]]''), [[-ducendo#Italian|-ducendo]] (''for verbs ending in [[-durre#Italian|-durre]]'')
*Norwegian: [[-ende]]
{{bottom}}

===Etymology 3===
Old English [[-ing#Old English|-ing]].

====Suffix====
'''-ing'''
# ''(not productive)'' forming (originally masculine) derivative nouns, with the sense ‘son of, belonging to’, as patronymics or diminutives
#:''[[atheling]]'', ''[[gelding]]''

